# 1. CREATE CALLING DEFINITIONS
# â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•
echo "[CALLINGS-01] Installing calling definitions..."
mkdir -p /etc/alfred/callings

cat > /etc/alfred/callings/README.md << 'README'
# Alfred Linux 7.77 â€” The Four Callings

Every machine in the Kingdom has a calling â€” a purpose it serves.
All callings share the same foundation: Bible, encryption, mesh, security.
What differs is the gifts installed on top.

## Callings

- **Desktop** â€” Full Kingdom experience. Worship player, Bible reader,
  Alfred Browser, Alfred IDE, 8K wallpapers. For the person at the screen.

- **Server** â€” Headless. SSH + Cockpit web panel. No desktop, lean, fast.
  For always-on machines serving the Kingdom quietly.

- **Relay** â€” Mesh network hub. Routes traffic for Kingdom users.
  WireGuard relay, Syncthing hub, radio streaming.

- **Forge** â€” GPU compute. AI inference, builds, heavy lifting.
  Auto-detects NVIDIA/AMD, installs drivers, Ollama ready.

- **Hearth** â€” Simple, warm, peaceful. Bible reader, music player,
  photos, letters. For the widow, the elder, the child â€” those
  who want rest, not complexity.

## Changing Your Calling

  alfred-calling status      â€” Show current calling
  alfred-calling switch      â€” Change calling (requires reboot)
  alfred-calling list        â€” Show all available callings
README

# â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•
